      "description": "Catalog item fulfillment orchestrator (DOC-09 \u00a7UC-8). Generic engine that fulfils ANY catalog item by reading its template from itsm.catalog_item, decomposing the request into a task DAG via a single LLM call, and orchestrating execution through LangGraph (parallel waves via Send, approval gates via interrupt(), retry with backoff, saga compensation on cancel). Both portal-submit and chat paths land in the same handler \u2014 parity guaranteed by `tools.fulfill_request`. Mock integration adapters (AD / email / VPN / GitHub / license / procurement) swap to real APIs via the IntegrationAdapter Protocol without handler changes. Tracks SR \u2192 RITM \u2192 tasks \u2192 approvals in itsm.* substrate; emits per-task OTel spans + per-tenant cost; lifecycle-gated by step-1 state machine (ships as draft, activated by quality gate).",
